@section head {
	<style>
		.outline .outline {
			background:#EFEFEF;
			text-align:center;
			line-height: 2em;
			padding: 0;
		}
	</style>
	<link rel="Stylesheet" href="~/content/site/ext/mediatest.css" type="text/css" />
}
<div class="page-content">
	<div class="col text-justify">
		<section>
			<h1>Structure</h1>
			<h2>Columns (width constraints)</h2>
			<p>Fluid layouts are provided with a <code>.col[#]</code> class.</p>
			<div class="outline example">
				<div>
					<div class="col1"><div class="outline">.col1</div></div>
					<div class="col2"><div class="outline">.col2</div></div>
					<div class="col2"><div class="outline">.col2</div></div>
					<div class="col3"><div class="outline">.col3</div></div>
					<div class="col3-2"><div class="outline">.col3-2</div></div>
					<div class="col4"><div class="outline">.col4</div></div>
					<div class="col4"><div class="outline">.col4</div></div>
					<div class="col4"><div class="outline">.col4</div></div>
					<div class="col4"><div class="outline">.col4</div></div>
					<div class="col5"><div class="outline">.col5</div></div>
					<div class="col5"><div class="outline">.col5</div></div>
					<div class="col5"><div class="outline">.col5</div></div>
					<div class="col5"><div class="outline">.col5</div></div>
					<div class="col5"><div class="outline">.col5</div></div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2>Rows (height constraints)</h2>
			<p>
				Columns <code>.col[#]</code> and rows are independent of each other. A <code>.row</code> (without
				height constraint applies the negative left margin for cols to align nicely in the <code>.page-content</code>.
			</p>
			<p>All height constraints will be removed on small resolutions.</p>
			<ul class="list-style-none">
				<li>
					<code>.row</code> - wraps content without any height constraint.
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>.row5</code> - 1/5<sup>th</sup> height constraint on the row (small, 5em).
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>.row4</code> - 1/4<sup>th</sup> height constraint on the row (medium, 10em).
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>.row3</code> - 1/3<sup>rd</sup> height constraint on the row (large, 15em).
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>.row2</code> - 1/2 height constraint on the row (larger, 20em).
				</li>
				<li>
					<code>.row1</code> - Maximum height constraint on the row (25em).
				</li>
			</ul>
			
			<h2>Helper Classes</h2>
			<div class="col2">
				<h3>Display</h3>
				<ul class="list-style-none">
					<li>
						<code>.hide</code> - sets the display property to none.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.stretch</code> - sets a 100% width.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.nowrap</code> - set the white-space to nowrap.
					</li>
				</ul>
				<h3>Floats</h3>
				<ul class="list-style-none">
					<li>
						<code>.float-left</code> - sets float to left.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.float-right</code> - sets float to right.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.clear</code> - clears both left and right floats.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.clearfix</code> - addes a clearfix.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="col2">
				<h3>Padding and Margin</h3>
				<ul class="list-style-none">
					<li>
						<code>.pad</code> - adds padding to all sides.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.pad-left</code> - adds left padding.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.pad-right</code> - adds right padding.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.pad-top</code> - adds top padding.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.pad-bottom</code> - adds bottom padding.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.margin</code> - adds a margin to all sides.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.margin-left</code> - adds a left margin.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.margin-right</code> - adds a right margin.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.margin-top</code> - adds a top margin.
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>.margin-bottom</code> - adds a bottom margin.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h1>Layout</h1>
			<h2>Page Layout</h2>
			<p>The page has six layout options: default, constrained, or centered - with or without a sidebar. </p>
			<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;section class="page">
	&lt;header class="page-header">&lt;h1>Page Title&lt;/h1>&lt;/header>
	&lt;div class="page-body">
		&lt;aside class="page-aside">&lt;/aside>
		&lt;div class="page-content">&lt;/div>
	&lt;/div>
&lt;/section>
</pre>
			<p>
				The <code>.page</code> section can have a <code>.centered</code> class to constrain the width and center the page.
			</p>
			<p>
				The <code>.page-aside</code> is optional if needing a sidebar.
			</p>

			
			<h2>Frame</h2>
			<p>The page is surrounded by a frame and should be placed within the <code>#frame-body</code> element.</p>
			<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;div id="frame">
	&lt;header id="frame-header>...&lt;/header>
	&lt;div id="frame-body>...&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
</pre>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h1>Responsive Support</h1>
			<h2>Media Queries</h2>
			<p>Resize the screen to see the base targeted resolutions.</p>
			<div class="outline example">
				<div class="mediatest">Media</div>
			</div>
			<p>These are the base targeted breakpoints.</p>
			<p>Internet Explorer 7 does not support the content property so follow the colors for media query application.</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>Black</strong> - No media queries applied
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Yellow</strong> - Phone
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Blue</strong> - Tablet
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Green</strong> - Desktop
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Red</strong> - Widescreen
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</div>
</div>
